@@ -287,6 +287,10 @@ newlines and Shift+Enter are chat prompt line breaks. A plain Enter submits the
 When an agent chat is selected in command mode, `/` focuses the chat, seeds the chat buffer with
 `/`, and enters insert mode so `/status`-style input submits through the same selected-agent chat
 path.
+Command mode supports visual text selection in the focused pane: `v` starts character selection,
+`V` starts line selection, `Ctrl-V` starts block selection, `h/j/k/l` and arrow keys move the
+selection cursor, and `y` or `Y` yank selected text. Yanked text is stored in terminal UI state and
+emitted through an OSC 52 terminal clipboard sequence on the next rendered frame.
 
 The terminal app maps a session to a left-pane `READY` marker when the controller exposes no loading
 state for that session. `TerminalUi` queues one terminal bell when a chat transitions into the ready
